{
  "text": "For the left system, its equilibrium E 2 := (\u03c7, \u22124\u03c7) is a stable focus. Moreover, O is a boundary equilibrium if \u03c7 = 0 and an invisible (resp. a visible) tangency point if \u03c7 = 1 (resp. \u01eb), i.e., the orbit of the left system passing through O is tangent to x = 0 at O from right (resp. left) side. Then there exists\u1e91 0 \u2265 0 such that the forward orbit of the left system starting from (0, z 0 ) with z 0 \u2265\u1e91 0 evolves in the left half plane and reaches again y-axis at a point of form (0, z 1 ) with z 1 \u2264 0 after a finite time t \u2212 \u2265 0. Choosing\u1e91 0 as the minimum one, we define the left Poincar\u00e9 map P L (z 0 ) := z 1 . From [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] again, the expression of P L is given by z 0 (t \u2212 ) = \u03c7 e 2t \u2212 \u2212 cos t \u2212 \u2212 2 sin t \u2212 sin t \u2212 , z 1 (t \u2212 ) = \u2212\u03c7 e \u22122t \u2212 \u2212 cos t \u2212 + 2 sin t \u2212 sin t \u2212 if \u03c7 = \u01eb, 1 and P L (z 0 ) = \u2212e \u22122\u03c0 z 0 if \u03c7 = 0, where t \u2212 \u2208 (\u03c0,t \u2212 ] (resp. [0, \u03c0)) for \u03c7 = \u01eb (resp. 1) andt \u2212 \u2208 (\u03c0, 2\u03c0) satisfies z 1 (t \u2212 ) = 0. In addition, we hav\u00ea",
